# Keep local build artifacts OUT of the Docker build context.
#
# Without this, `COPY <project>/ <project>/` copies the host's bin/ and obj/
# into the image. The Windows obj/ contains static-web-asset manifests
# (staticwebassets.build.json) that reference framework assets by absolute
# host paths, e.g.
#   C:\Users\...\.nuget\packages\microsoft.aspnetcore.app.internal.assets\...\_framework\blazor.web.js
# On the Linux build those paths don't exist, so `dotnet publish --no-restore`
# silently drops _framework/* (blazor.web.js, blazor.server.js) from wwwroot.
# Excluding bin/obj forces the container to use its own clean restore.
**/bin/
**/obj/

# VCS / CI / IDE / local tooling — not needed in the image.
.git/
.github/
.vs/
.vscode/
**/*.user
.temp/
.tempbuild/
.agents/
.claude/
